<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="181" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1369,1754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1549,1574]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Comment.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Hu &amp; Li, 2010" authorityName="Hu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2010" box="[598,914,1549,1574]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nazeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sadanarii">
<emphasis box="[598,739,1549,1573]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">N. sadanarii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hu" box="[747,914,1549,1574]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181" refString="Hu, J. Y., Li, L. Z., Tian, M. X. &amp; Cao, G. H. (2010) Additional two new species of the genus Nazeris from China (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 16 (1), 109 - 114." type="journal article" year="2010">Hu &amp; Li, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[984,1054,1549,1574]" country="China" name="Anhui" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Anhui</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1111,1316,1549,1574]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Zhejiang province</collectingRegion>
in general appearance, but is distinguished by the relatively denser setae of male sternite VII and by the apically acute ventral process of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="181" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1369,1754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,562,1657,1682]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Distribution and habitat data.</emphasis>
This species has been recorded from Mufu Shan in northeastern 
<collectingRegion box="[1312,1387,1658,1681]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Hunan</collectingRegion>
and Jiugong Shan in southern 
<collectingRegion box="[443,511,1693,1718]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Hubei</collectingRegion>
(new province record, 
<figureCitation box="[773,856,1693,1718]" captionStart="FIGURE22" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1907,1929]" captionTargetBox="[150,1437,844,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1437,844,1886]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE22. Map showing the distribution of Nazeris in Luoxiao Mountain Range A—N. inaequalis; B—N. proiectus; C—N. luoxiaoshanus; D—N. pengzhongi; E—N. divisus; F—N. paradivisus; G—N. xiaobini; H—N. congchaoi; I—N. nannani; J— N.rufus; K—N.ziweii; L—N.daweishanus; M—N.prominens; N—N.zekani; O—N. yipingae; P—N. jiaweii." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1143943/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). The specimens were collected by sifting decaying leaf litter in mixed forests at altitudes of 
<quantity box="[607,765,1729,1754]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.375" metricValueMax="1.55" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="181" unit="m" value="1375.0" valueMax="1550.0" valueMin="1200.0">1200–1550 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
